name: PARNASO #2 - Half way up
description:
My wife and I knew that this hiking would be demanding but it was a matter of overcoming our limits. At this point we'd walked a lot, almost a mile of irregular inclined trails. The weather was a little bit on the muggy side, switching between sunny and cloudy as with lots of clouds were passing by. Sweating, hungry and thirsty we stopped, relaxed a little bit and enjoyed the view. We saw god in the little things once again.

About the series: Pictures taken in and around the Serra dos Órgãos National Park ('Parque Nacional da Serra dos Órgãos' in portuguese or its abbreviation 'PARNASO'), located in the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, and covers a huge area across four municipalities.

Equipment: Sony Alpha A6500 + Sony E 18-135mm F/3.5-5.6 OSS
Location: Petrópolis, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
